place.name: FREETHORPE
place.gazetteerText: FREETHORPE, a parish in Blofield district, Norfolk; near the river Yare, 2 miles N of Reedham r. station, and 4 S by E of Acle. Post town, Reedham, under Norwich. Acres, 869. Real property, £2, 177. Pop., 425. Houses, 94. The property is divided among a few. The living is a vicarage, annexed to the rectory of Reeding, in the diocese of Norwich. The church is ancient, and was recently restored. There is a Primitive Methodist chapel. . (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
